<br>
Rogues haven't seen a decent damage increase since Kunark, and with the recent &quot;rebalancing&quot; for casters, it's not only possible for them to completely annihilate my dps, it happens on a nightly basis. For example, Diabo Xi Xin Thall parsed out for me to be 75.6 dps. The best wizard output on the same mob (using garrisons, he did not have destruction of ice), in the same amount of time was 168 dps. I could be mistaken here, but that seems just a BIT out of whack. For everything that wizards get with respect to utility, and ability to solo, for them to so utterly destroy our DPS is retarded. &quot;Caster balancing&quot; has thus far seemed to me to be random at best, and destructive with respect to game balance at worst.<br>
<br>
In addition to wizards oudamaging rogues, it's 100% possible, and likely for necros to be able to do the same with the new dot changes, using 4-5 dots. I'm not saying that it will happen every time, but with certainty, it's possible.<br>
<br>
Rogues happen to offer very little except for damage. We can sneak around, and I'm happy that they've finally decided to give us the bonus of being able to hide/sneak past mobs that others would be seen by. That's great, though it shouldn't have to be something we buy extra, it's helpful. But when you compare rogue utility to other classes, we fall short on almost every level. Without a fairly decent increase in damage in PoP, it's not really going to be worth looking to play our class if you're looking for some sort of return for your time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub117.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jake0>Jake0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/02 3:00:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12012.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> 75dps? heh,  get more atk buddy, that's not so uber even though DXX has insane mitigation. Rogues can outdamage wizards, it just takes way too much effort, you can slap a gimp wizard, give him a few spells and some mod rods and he'll tack on major dps whereas a rogue needs a bst, necro, bard, actually move around and follow the mob's back when you can't corner the mob, feral avatar, many vengeance items, and other @#%$... we do need a dps increase though, a rogue that actually gets all of those buffs should freakin destroy a mob rather than just barely outdamage a wizard.<br>
