Everyone at a raid gets buffs - the idea is to get max effectiveness from the overall raid by making sure each person at the raid does the most effective task for their class.  Some classes are getting max effectiveness by focussing on wizards.  Mages summoning rods to give to a wizard aren't doing their own DD.  Necros passing along mana after they stick DoTs aren't doing their DD.  Bards don't get much DD, but passing along mana to casters is most effective when it includes wizards and clerics.  Healers watching wizards that mod aren't doing whatever else they could be doing.  <br>
<br>
There's no way a wizard without all that assistance could come close to the DPS reported.  Currently, a decently equipped Rogue only needs a compenent MT, some buffs, and a heal now and then to be at their max effectiveness.<br>
<br>
I really don't think it unbalanced that by having some classes focus on servicing wizards that the overall DPS of the raid goes up.  I would like to see something similiar added to Rogues though.  Rogues should be able to do comparable damage if the same attention were focussed on them.<br>
